args: *pant* *pant* She's nowhere to be seen...\nOh, Angie, where have you gone?!
Have ya managed to track down that\nadorable little moppet of yours yet?
I ain't got time for yer crap, Bareed!
Not sure I'd take that tone with me,\nold friend. 'Specially not if ya wanna\nsee that kid again.

Now THERE'S the Bloodfist I remember!
Never were able to control yer temper.
Still, the girl is safe as houses back at
my place, so don't ya worry none.

Oh, but I've MISSED ya, Gauld!
And no, I ain't kidnapped no one.
Just think of it as yer old pal
keepin' a young girl safe.
But if ya want her to stay all pretty and\nunharmed, yer gonna do what I say!
Gah ha ha! Oh, it's so damn hard to tell\nya no, Gauld. It really is. Buuuut...no.
Not unless ya come back to be my\nright-hand man with the Burly Boys!
Why are you so obsessed with me?\nYOU'RE the boss now! I turned all\nthat over to you and walked away!
You're the only one who thinks that way.

We got problems comin' at us from
every which'a way, and all folks can
say is that they'd be done and dusted
if the ol' Bloodfist was still around.
So that's why they need to see YOU\nbackin' ME! Ease their minds, like.
Gah ha ha! Ya see? This ain't so hard!\nJust fall in line and do what I say,\nand nobody's gotta get hurt.
I'm sorry, Angie. I really am.\nBut I never meant to lie to you.
I was just waiting for you to get a little\nolder before I told you the whole truth.
I just... I can't believe it.\nHow could you keep it a secret?
I was scared what you'd think of me\nif I told you the whole truth.
I thought you might just quit\noutta my life for good.
But that was cowardice, and it caused\nyou pain. I can't tell you how sorry I am.
Can you please forgive me?\nAnd maybe...call me Gramps again?
Okay, think that's enough'a the heartfelt\nreunion! Get over here, little miss.
Bareed! If ya lay another finger on her,\nyer gonna deal with ME!
I give the orders here, Gauld!\nYou shut up and take 'em!
Ah, hell! She's havin' a fit!
Bareed, please. I'm sorry. You just...\nYou have to stay calm in front of her.\nNo violence or harsh words. Okay?
GAAAH HA HA! Now who whoulda thought\nthe Bloodfist would bow his head to ME?!
But I ain't an unreasonable man.\nIf ya want the kid healthy and happy,\nya just gotta do what I say. Easy, no?
Then for starters, ya can sit right here,\nshut yer yap, and not move. Got it?
...Oh, don't lookit me like that! I got a\nmountain'a work for yaâ€”you'll be outta\nhere before ya have time to get bored.
I'm sorry, Angie. This is all my fault.
I can't let that go on any longer.\nEven if it meansâ€”
The Reaper! Why are you here?
I told you, I'm trying to put an end\nto the Burly Boys.
You planning to kill Bareed?\nAnd am I on the list now, too?
...It's no surprise it's come to this for\nBareed. But please, just not right now!
I've seen people like her before.\nThat's a girl with some deep hurt.
And it's all because of me.
Her real dad was one of the Burly Boysâ€”\nguy named Girard. He was a bad sort,\nand that's puttin' it lightly.

He'd throw the Burly Boys name around
to lord over people, then take off the
second things got hairy. Never kept a
promise. Only thought about himself.
But the Burly Boys was made for guys\nlike that. We were all bad, more or less.
But then he crossed the one line we had.\nHe killed one of our own.
He knew the hell that would come for him,\nso he stabbed us in the back and sold us\nout to a rival organization.
As the boss, I couldn't let it slide.\nI tracked him down and...dealt with it.
...Yes. Angie saw my arm covered in her\nown father's blood.
Now, she was just a baby back then,\nso she doesn't really remember it.\nNot clearly, anyway.
But she's terrified by violence. Terrified.\nEven a raised voice is enough to send\nher into a crazed fit.
We had it rough as kids ourselves.\nUseless parents tossed us out and\nforced us into a life on the street.
We started the Burly Boys in order to have\na place lost boys like us could make a\nlittle coin. Soon enough, we were thriving.
Before I knew it, I'd gone from BEING\nan unhappy kid to MAKING them.
Once I realized that, I knew the\ngroup couldn't continue.
So you stopped being the Bloodfist.
I didn't need an arm covered in bloodâ€”\nI needed one that could comfort a child.
Guess maybe that was my own way\nto run away. From the Burly Boys,\nfrom my past...all of it.
I should have used my fist to beat the\nBoys into shape. Instead, I destroyed it.
My life's just one mistake after another...
If you make a mistake, make it right.\nIt's not too late to do that now.
Heh. Strange world indeed where I'm\nbeing comforted by the Reaper.
It's precisely because of the life I've lived\nthat I wish for a peaceful and happy\nworldâ€”the life I failed to obtain.
Suffering makes for strange bedfellows.\nStill, you're rightâ€”if I'm going to make\nthis right, I have to start now.
I need to find Angie and Bareed.\nWill you help me, Reaper?
Just hang on, Angie...\nGramps is comin' for ya!
